uote-contentid=\u0022202289\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221620501897\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002298447\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022YNM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n53 minutes ago, YNM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you heard about continents ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust bigger islands.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n***\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA great map. Thanks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Starman4308","CreatedById":122674,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-05-08T23:44:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would almost certainly be cheaper and safer to have the nuclear power plant generate fuel on land (e.g. via the Fischer-Tropsch process), and run the aircraft on that fuel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere might be tactical reasons to have a nuclear-powered military aircraft, e.g. to have a very long-endurance bomber, but midair refueling makes that much less important as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe big, expensive nuclear reactor with loads of radioactive fuel can power aircraft perfectly well without ever leaving the ground.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-05-08T23:45:42Z\u0022 title=\u002205/08/2021 11:45  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EMay 8, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Starman4308\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}